  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To investigate the severity of secondary Raynaud's disease-related attacks during the 14 days
      2101 dosing period.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      1. Number and cumulative duration of Raynaud's attacks.

        2. Adverse events and changes in vital signs.

        3. SLx-2101 pharmacokinetic parameters derived after dosing on Day 1 and Day maximum plasma
           concentration (Cmax), area under the plasma concentration-time curve (AUC0-4), time to
           Cmax (tmax), and accumulation ratio
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
